      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical Information</head>
         <p>Mr. Buford was the negotiator between the City of Richmond
         and the County of Henrico who was responsible for a twenty
         year utilities contract. He was also the chairman of the Task
         Force that evaluated the need and potential for expanded port
         facilities in the central Virginia area.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The collection consists of correspondence, reports,
         memoranda, minutes and plans concerning the negotiation of a
         water-sewer agreement between the City of Richmond and the
         County of Henrico and the working papers of the James River
         Port Study Task Force.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>The correspondence is filed in reverse chronological
            order.</p>
         </arrangement>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Organization</head>
            <p>All other materials are in original order and labelled
            by Mr. Buford. 
            <lb />Series I--Richmond-Henrico Water Contract (n.d.,
            1966-1968); 
            <lb />Series II--James River Port Study Task Force (n.d.,
            1983-1988). 
            <lb /></p>
         </arrangement>
      </arrangement>
